\par 3. Installation
\par 
\par ignitionServer should have came with an installer. There are two versions of the installer, one
\par for Windows 9x and one for Windows NT. The Windows 9x installer will install on NT systems, but
\par the ignitionServer Monitor will not be installed. The Windows NT installer will ONLY work on NT
\par systems, because the ignitionServer Monitor uses critical NT system calls.
\par 
\par Windows 9x includes: Windows 95, Windows 98, Windows 98 SE, and Windows Millenium Edition
\par Windows NT includes: Windows NT 4, Windows 2000, Windows XP, and Windows Server 2003
\par 
\par This _might_ run under UNIX/Linux with Wine, but you will have to play with it yourself (i.e. do
\par not post to the support tracker; WE CAN NOT HELP YOU!)
\par 
\par Remember to disable DIE in your ircx.conf file.
